obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (28708)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Persons carrying on industry, etc., not to allow emission of air pollutants in excess of the standard laid down by State Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. The words "carrying on any industry specified in the Schedule or" omitted by Act 47 of 1987, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28708&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `No person ^1`
  line `**** operating any industrial plant, in any air`
  line `pollution control area shall discharge or cause or permit to be discharged the emission of any air pollutant`
  line `in excess of the standards laid down by the State Board under clause (g) of sub-section (1) of section 17.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (28709)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 24
  title `Power of Board to make application to court for restraining persons from causing air pollution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28709&sectionno=22A&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[22A. Power of Board to make application to court for restraining person from causing air`
  line `pollution.--(1) Where it is apprehended by a Board that emission of any air pollutant, in excess of the`
  line `standards laid down by the State Board under clause (g) of sub-section (1) of section 17, is likely to occur`
  line `by reason of any person operating an industrial plant or otherwise in any air pollution control area, the`
  line `Board may make an application to a court, not inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial`
  line `Magistrate of the first class for restraining such person from emitting such air pollutant.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the application under sub-section (1), the court may make such order as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Where under sub-section (2), the court makes an order restraining any person from discharging or`
  line `causing or permitting to be discharged the emission of any air pollutant, it may, in that order,--`
  line
  line `(a) direct such person to desist from taking such action as is likely to cause emission;`
  line
  line `(b) authorise the Board, if the direction under clause (a) is not complied with by the person to`
  line `whom such direction is issued, to implement the direction in such manner as may be specified by the`
  line court.
  line
  line `(4) All expenses incurred by the Board in implementing the directions of the court under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (3) shall be recoverable from the person concerned as arrears of land revenue or of public`
  line demand.]
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (28710)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title `Furnishing of information to State Board and other agencies in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. The words "air pollution control" omitted by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28710&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in`
  line `any ^1`
  line `*** area the emission of any air pollutant into the atmosphere in excess of the standards laid down`
  line `by the State Board occurs or is apprehended to occur due to accident or other unforeseen act or event, the`
  line `person in charge of the premises from where such emission occurs or is apprehended to occur shall`
  line `forthwith intimate the fact of such occurrence or the apprehension of such occurrence to the State Board`
  line `and to such authorities or agencies as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of information with respect to the fact or the apprehension of any occurrence of the`
  line `nature referred to in sub-section (1), whether through intimation under that sub-section or otherwise, the`
  line `State Board and the authorities or agencies shall, as early as practicable, cause such remedial measure to`
  line `be taken as are necessary to mitigate the emission of such air pollutants.`
  line
  line `(3) Expenses, if any, incurred by the State Board, authority or agency with respect to the remedial`
  line `measures referred to in sub-section (2) together with interest (at such reasonable rate, as the State`
  line `Government may, by order, fix) from the date when a demand for the expenses is made until it is paid,`
  line `may be recovered by that Board, authority or agency from the person concerned, as arrears of land`
  line `revenue, or of public demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (28711)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power of entry and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28711&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, any person`
  line `empowered by a State Board in this behalf shall have a right to enter, at all reasonable times with such`
  line `assistance as he considers necessary, any place--`
  line
  line `(a) for the purpose of performing any of the functions of the State Board entrusted to him;`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of determining whether and if so in what manner, any such functions are to be`
  line `performed or whether any provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder or any notice, order,`
  line `direction or authorisation served, made, given or granted under this Act is being or has been complied`
  line with;
  line
  line `(c) for the purpose of examining and testing any control equipment, industrial plant, record,`
  line `register, document or any other material object or for conducting a search of any place in which he`
  line `has reason to believe that an offence under this Act or the rules made thereunder has been or is being`
  line `or is about to be committed and for seizing any such control equipment, industrial plant, record,`
  line `register, document or other material object if he has reasons to believe that it may furnish evidence of`
  line `the commission of an offence punishable under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person ^1`
  line `*** operating any control equipment or any industrial plant, in an air pollution`
  line `control area shall be bound to render all assistance to the person empowered by the State Board under`
  line `sub-section (1) for carrying out the functions under that sub-section and if he fails to do so without any`
  line `reasonable cause or excuse, he shall be guilty of an offence under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person willfully delays or obstructs any person empowered by the State Board under`
  line `sub-section (1) in the discharge of his duties, he shall be guilty of an offence under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), or, in relation to the State of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir*, or any area, in which that Code is not in force, the provisions of any corresponding`
  line `law in force in that State or area, shall, so far as may be, apply to any search or seizure under this section`
  line `as they apply to any search or seizure made under the authority of a warrant issued under section 94 of the`
  line `said Code or, as the case may be, under the corresponding provisions of the said law.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "carrying on any industry specified in the Schedule and every person" omitted by Act 47 of 1987, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (28712)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to obtain information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28712&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of carrying out the functions entrusted to it, the`
  line `State Board or any officer empowered by it in that behalf may call for any information (including`
  line `information regarding the types of air pollutants emitted into the atmosphere and the level of the emission`
  line `of such air pollutants) from the occupier or any other person carrying on any industry or operating any`
  line `control equipment or industrial plant and for the purpose of verifying the correctness of such information,`
  line `the State Board or such officer shall have the right to inspect the premises where such industry, control`
  line `equipment or industrial plant is being carried on or operated.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (28713)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to take samples of air or emission and procedure to be followed in connection therewith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28713&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Board or any officer empowered by it in this behalf shall have power to take, for`
  line `the purpose of analysis, samples of air or emission from any chimney, flue or duct or any other outlet in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The result of any analysis of a sample of emission taken under sub-section (1) shall not be`
  line `admissible in evidence in any legal proceeding unless the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4) are`
  line `complied with.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), when a sample of emission is taken for analysis under`
  line `sub-section (1), the person taking the sample shall--`
  line
  line `(a) serve on the occupier or his agent, a notice, then and there, in such form as may be prescribed,`
  line `of his intention to have it so analysed;`
  line
  line `(b) in the presence of the occupier or his agent, collect a sample of emission for analysis;`
  line
  line `(c) cause the sample to be placed in a container or containers which shall be marked and sealed`
  line `and shall also be signed both by the person taking the sample and the occupier or his agent;`
  line
  line `(d) send, without delay, the container or containers to the laboratory established or recognised by`
  line `the State Board under section 17 or, if a request in that behalf is made by the occupier or his agent`
  line `when the notice is served on him under clause (a), to the laboratory established or specified under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 28.`
  line
  line `(4) When a sample of emission is taken for analysis under sub-section (1) and the person taking the`
  line `sample serves on the occupier or his agent, a notice under clause (a) of sub-section (3), then,--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where the occupier or his agent wilfully absents himself, the person taking the`
  line `sample shall collect the sample of emission for analysis to be placed in a container or containers`
  line `which shall be marked and sealed and shall also be signed by the person taking the sample, and`
  line
  line `(b) in a case where the occupier or his agent is present at the time of taking the sample but refuses`
  line `to sign the marked and sealed container or containers of the sample of emission as required under`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (3), the marked and sealed container or containers shall be signed by the`
  line `person taking the sample,`
  line
  line `and the container or containers shall be sent without delay by the person taking the sample for analysis to`
  line `the laboratory established or specified under sub-section (1) of section 28 and such person shall inform`
  line `the Government analyst appointed under sub-section (1) of section 29, in writing, about the wilful`
  line `absence of the occupier or his agent, or, as the case may be, his refusal to sign the container or containers.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (28714)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Reports of the result of analysis on samples taken under section 26.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28714&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a sample of`
  line `emission has been sent for analysis to the laboratory established or recognised by the State Board, the`
  line `Board analyst appointed under sub-section (2) of section 29 shall analyse the sample and submit a report`
  line `in the prescribed form of such analysis in triplicate to the State Board.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the report under sub-section (1), one copy of the report shall be sent by the State`
  line `Board to the occupier or his agent referred to in section 26, another copy shall be preserved for production`
  line `before the court in case any legal proceedings are taken against him and the other copy shall be kept by`
  line `the State Board.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a sample has been sent for analysis under clause of sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 26 to any laboratory mentioned therein, the Government analyst referred to in the said`
  line `sub-section (4) shall analyse the sample and submit a report in the prescribed form of the result of the`
  line `analysis in triplicate to the State Board which shall comply with the provisions of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Any cost incurred in getting any sample analysed at the request of the occupier or his agent as`
  line `provided in clause (d) of sub-section (3) of section 26 or when he wilfully absents himself or refuses to`
  line `sign the marked and sealed container or containers of sample of emission under sub-section (4) of that`
  line `section, shall be payable by such occupier or his agent and in case of default the same shall be recoverable`
  line `from him as arrears of land revenue or of public demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (28715)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `State Air Laboratory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28715&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line Gazette,--
  line
  line `(a) establish one or more State Air Laboratories; or`
  line
  line `(b) specify one or more laboratories or institutes as State Air Laboratories to carry out the`
  line `functions entrusted to the State Air Laboratory under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, after consultation with the State Board, make rules prescribing--`
  line
  line `(a) the functions of the State Air Laboratory;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure for the submission to the said Laboratory of samples of air or emission for`
  line `analysis or tests, the form of the Laboratory's report thereon and the fees payable in respect of such`
  line report;
  line
  line `(c) such other matters as may be necessary or expedient to enable that Laboratory to carry out its`
  line functions.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (28716)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title Analysis.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28716&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint such`
  line `persons as it thinks fit and having the prescribed qualifications to be Government analysts for the purpose`
  line `of analysis of samples of air or emission sent for analysis to any laboratory established or specified under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 28.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of section 14, the State Board may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, and with the approval of the State Government, appoint such persons as it thinks fit and`
  line `having the prescribed qualifications to be Board analysts for the purpose of analysis of samples of air or`
  line `emission sent for analysis to any laboratory established or recognised under section 17.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (28717)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Reports of analysis.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28717&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Any document purporting to be a report signed by a Government analyst`
  line `or, as the case may be, a State Board analyst may be used as evidence of the facts stated therein in any`
  line `proceeding under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (28718)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28718&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order made by the State Board under this Act may,`
  line `within thirty day from the date on which the order is communicated to him, prefer an appeal to such`
  line `authority (hereinafter referred to as the Appellate Authority) as the State Government may think fit to`
  line `constitute:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Authority may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days if such authority is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the`
  line `appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Authority shall consist of a single person or three persons as the State Government`
  line `may think fit to be appointed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The form and the manner in which an appeal may be preferred under sub-section (1), the fees`
  line `payable for such appeal and the procedure to be followed by the Appellate Authority shall be such as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of an appeal preferred under sub-section (1), the Appellate Authority shall, after giving`
  line `the appellant and the State Board an opportunity of being heard, dispose of the appeal as expeditiously as`
  line possible.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (28719)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28719&sectionno=31A&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[31A. Power to give directions.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, but subject`
  line `to the provisions of this Act, and to any directions that the Central Government may give in this behalf, a`
  line `Board may, in the exercise of its powers and performance of its functions under this Act, issue any`
  line `directions in writing to any person, officer or authority, and such person, officer or authority shall be`
  line `bound to comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the avoidance of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power to issue directions`
  line `under this section includes the power to direct--`
  line
  line `(a) the closure, prohibition or regulation of any industry, operation or process; or`
  line
  line `(b) the stoppage or regulation of supply of electricity, water or any other service.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_b:
  sectionId (57337)
  sectionNo 31B
  orderNo 35
  title `Appeal to National Green Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 2010, s. 36 and Schedule III (w.e.f. 18-10-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=57337&sectionno=31B&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_31_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[31B. Appeal to National Green Tribunal.—Any person aggrieved by an order or decision of the`
  line `Appellate Authority under section 31, made on or after the commencement of the National Green`
  line `Tribunal Act, 2010, may file an appeal to the National Green Tribunal established under section 3 of the`
  line `National Green Tribunal Act, 2010, in accordance with the provisions of that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (28720)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 36
  title `Contribution by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 15, ibid.,for "State Board for the Prevention and Control of water Pollution" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28720&sectionno=32&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation`
  line `made by Parliament by law in this behalf make in each financial year such contributions to the State`
  line `Boards as it may think necessary to enable the State Boards to perform their functions under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to any ^1`
  line `[State Pollution Control Board] constituted`
  line `under section 4 of the Water (Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1974 (6 of 1974), which is`
  line `empowered by that Act to expend money from its fund thereunder also for performing its functions, under`
  line `any law for the time being in force relating to the prevention, control or abatement of air pollution.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (28721)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 37
  title `Fund of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 15, for "State Board for the Prevention and Control of Water Pollution" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28721&sectionno=33&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Board shall have its own fund for the purposes of this Act and`
  line `all sums which may, from time to time, be paid to it by theCentral Government and all other receipts (by`
  line `way of contributions, if any, from the State Government, fees, gifts, grants, donations benefactions or`
  line `otherwise) of that Board shall be carried to the fund of the Board and all payments by the Board shall be`
  line `made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) Every State Board may expend such sums as it thinks fit for performing its functions under this`
  line `Act and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the fund of that Board.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall apply to any ^1`
  line `[State Pollution Control Board] constituted under`
  line `section 4 of the Water(Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1974 (6 of 1974), which is empowered`
  line `by that Act to expend money from its fund thereunder also for performing its functions, under any law for`
  line `the time being in force relating to the prevention, control or abatement of air pollution.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_a:
  sectionId (28722)
  sectionNo 33A
  orderNo 38
  title `Borrowing powers of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content
  footnotes `1 . Ins. by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28722&sectionno=33A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[33A. Borrowing powers of Board.--A Board may, with the consent of, or in accordance with the`
  line `terms of any general or special authority given to it by, the Central Government or, as the case may be,`
  line `the State Government, borrow money from any source by way of loans or issue of bonds, debentures or`
  line `such other instruments, as it may deem fit, for discharging all or any of its functions under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (28723)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 39
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28723&sectionno=34&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The Central Board or, as the case may be, the State Board shall, during each financial`
  line `year, prepare, in such form and at such time as may be prescribed, a budget in respect of the financial year`
  line `next ensuing showing the estimated receipt and expenditure under this Act, and copies thereof shall be`
  line `forwarded to the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (28724)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 40
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. bys. 17, ibid.,for section 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28724&sectionno=35&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[35. Annual report.-- (1) The Central Board shall, during each financial year, prepare, in such form`
  line `as may be prescribed, an annual report giving full account of its activities under this Act during the`
  line `previous financial year and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government within four`
  line `months from the last date of the previous financial year and that Government shall cause every such`
  line `report to be laid before both Houses of Parliament within nine months of the last date of the previous`
  line `financial year.`
  line
  line `(2) Every State Board shall, during each financial year, prepare, in such form as may be prescribed,`
  line `an annual report giving full account of its activities under this Act during the previous financial year and`
  line `copies thereof shall be forwarded to the State Government within four months from the last date of the`
  line `previous financial year and that Government shall cause every such report to be laid before the State`
  line `Legislature within a period of nine months from the last date of the previous financial year.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (28725)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 41
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28725&sectionno=36&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Board shall, in relation to its functions under this Act, maintain`
  line `proper accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited by an auditor duly qualified to act as an auditor of`
  line `companies under section 226 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
  line
  line `(3) The said auditor shall be appointed by the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State`
  line `Government on the advice of the Comptroller and Auditor General of India.`
  line
  line `(4) Every auditor appointed to audit the accounts of the Board under this Act shall have the right to`
  line `demand the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to`
  line `inspect any of the offices of the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) Every such auditor shall send a copy of his report together with an audited copy of the accounts to`
  line `the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government shall, as soon as may be after the receipt of the audit report under`
  line `sub-section (5), cause the same to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(7) The State Government shall, as soon as may be after the receipt of the audit report under`
  line `sub-section (5), cause the same to be laid before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (28726)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 42
  title `Failure to comply with the provisions of section 21 or section 22 or with the directions issued under section 31A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 18, for section 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28726&sectionno=37&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[37. Failure to comply with the provisions of section 21 or section 22 or with the directions`
  line `issued under section 31A.-- (1) whoever fails to comply with the provisions of section 21 or section 22`
  line `or directions issued under section 31A, shall, in respect of each such failure, be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year and six months but which may extend to`
  line `six years and with fine, and in case the failure continues, with an additional fine which may extend to five`
  line `thousand rupees for every day during which such failure continues after the conviction for the first such`
  line failure.
  line
  line `(2) If the failure referred to in sub-section (1) continues beyond a period of one year after the date of`
  line `conviction, the offender shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `two years but which may extend to seven years and with fine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (28727)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 43
  title `Penalties for certain acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28727&sectionno=38&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `^1[38. Penalties for certain acts.--(1) Whoever--`
  line
  line `(a) destroys, pulls down, removes, injures or defaces any pillar, post or stake fixed in the ground`
  line `or any notice or other matter put up, inscribed or placed, by or under the authority of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) obstructs any person acting under the orders or directions of the Board from exercising his`
  line `powers and performing his functions under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(c) damages any works or property belonging to the Board;`
  line
  line `(d) fails to furnish to the Board or any officer or other employee of the Board any information`
  line `required by the Board or such officer or other employee for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) fails to intimate the occurrence of the emission of air pollutants into the atmosphere in excess`
  line `of the standards laid down by the State Board or the apprehension of such occurrence, to the State`
  line `Board and other prescribed authorities or agencies as required under sub-section (1) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(f) fails in giving any information which he is required to give under this Act, makes a statement`
  line `which is false in any material particular,`
  line
  line `shall be liable to penalty which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees, but which may extend to fifteen`
  line `lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person continues contravention under sub-section (1), he shall be liable to additional`
  line `penalty of ten thousand rupees for every day during which such contravention continues.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sections 37 to 41, (w.e.f. 1-4-2024), earlier subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 18, for`
  line `section 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_38_a:
  sectionId (89167)
  sectionNo 38A
  orderNo 44
  title `Penalty for contravention by Government Department.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=89167&sectionno=38A&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[38A. Penalty for contravention by Government Department.--(1) Where contravention of any`
  line `provision of this Act has been committed by any Department of the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, the Head of the Department shall be liable to penalty equal to one month of his basic salary:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall not be liable for such contravention, if he proves that the contravention was`
  line `committed without his knowledge or instructions or that he exercised all due diligence to prevent such`
  line contravention.
  line
  line `(2) Where any contravention under sub-section (1) is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any`
  line `officer, other than the Head of the Department, the officer shall be liable to penalty equal to one month of`
  line `his basic salary:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall not be liable for the contravention, if he proves that he exercised all due`
  line `diligence to avoid such contravention.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sections 37 to 41, (w.e.f. 1-4-2024), earlier subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 18, for`
  line `section 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (28728)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 45
  title `Penalty for contravention of certain provisions of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28728&sectionno=39&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[39. Penalty for contravention of certain provisions of the Act.--If any person contravenes any`
  line `of the provisions of this Act or any order or direction issued thereunder, for which no penalty has been`
  line `provided for in this Act, shall be liable to penalty which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees, but`
  line `which may extend to fifteen lakh rupees, and where such contravention continues, he shall be liable to`
  line `additional penalty which may extend to ten thousand rupees for every day during which such`
  line `contravention continues.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sections 37 to 41, (w.e.f. 1-4-2024), earlier subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 18, for`
  line `section 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_39_a:
  sectionId (89168)
  sectionNo 39A
  orderNo 46
  title `Adjudicating officer`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=89168&sectionno=39A&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_39_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[39A. Adjudicating officer.--(1) The Central Government, for the purposes of determining the penalties under sections 37, 38, 38A and section 39, shall appoint an officer not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India or a Secretary to the State Government to be the adjudicating officer, to hold an inquiry and to impose the penalty in the manner, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may appoint as many adjudicating officers as may be required.`
  line
  line `(2) The adjudicating officer may summon and enforce the attendance of any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or to produce any document, which in the opinion of the adjudicating officer, may be useful for or relevant to the subject-matter of the inquiry and if, on such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person concerned has contravened the provisions of this Act, he may`
  line `determine such penalty as he thinks fit under the provisions of sections 37, 38, 38A or 39, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such penalty shall be imposed without giving the person concerned a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount of penalty imposed under the provisions of sections 37, 38, 38A and 39, shall be in`
  line `addition to the liability to pay relief or compensation under section 15 read with section 17 of the National`
  line `Green Tribunal Act, 2010 (19 of 2010).]`
obj_root_law_sections_39_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sections 37 to 41, (w.e.f. 1-4-2024), earlier subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 18, for`
  line `section 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_39_b:
  sectionId (89169)
  sectionNo 39B
  orderNo 47
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=89169&sectionno=39B&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_39_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[39B. Apeal.--(1) Whoever aggrieved by the order passed by the adjudicating officer under sections`
  line `37, 38, 38A or 39, may prefer an appeal to the National Green Tribunal established under section 3 of the`
  line `National Green Tribunal Act, 2010 (19 of 2010).`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within sixty days from the date on which the`
  line `copy of the order made by the adjudicating officer is received by the aggrieved person.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal may, after giving the parties to the appeal an opportunity of being heard, pass such`
  line `order as it thinks fit, confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an appeal is preferred against any order of the adjudicating officer under sub-section (1), it`
  line `shall not be entertained by the Tribunal unless the person has deposited with the Tribunal ten per cent. of`
  line `the amount of the penalty imposed by the adjudicating officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sections 37 to 41, (w.e.f. 1-4-2024), earlier subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 18, for`
  line `section 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_39_c:
  sectionId (89170)
  sectionNo 39C
  orderNo 48
  title `Penalty amount to be credited to Environmental Protection Fund.`
  content `^1[39C. Penalty amount to be credited to Environmental Protection Fund.--Where an adjudicating officer imposes penalty or additional penalty, as the case may be, under sections 37, 38, 38A or 39, the amount of such penalty shall be credited to the Environmental Protection Fund established under section 16 of the Environment (Protection) Act, 1986 (29 of 1986).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=89170&sectionno=39C&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_39_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sections 37 to 41, (w.e.f. 1-4-2024), earlier subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 18, for`
  line `section 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_39_d:
  sectionId (89171)
  sectionNo 39D
  orderNo 49
  title `Offences for failure to comply with provisions of section 21 and for failure to pay penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=89171&sectionno=39D&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_39_d_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39_d_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (28730)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 50
  title `Offences by Government Departments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28730&sectionno=41&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by any Department of Government, the Head of the Department shall be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall render such Head of the Department liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a Department of Government and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any officer, other than the Head`
  line `of the Department, such officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (28731)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 51
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28731&sectionno=42&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Government or any officer of the Government or any member or any officer or other`
  line `employee of the Board in respect of anything which is done or intended to be done in good faith in`
  line `pursuance of this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (28732)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 52
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 21, for section 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28732&sectionno=43&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[43. Cognizance of offences.--(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence under this Act`
  line `except on a complaint made by--`
  line
  line `(a) a Board or any officer authorised in this behalf by it; or`
  line
  line `(b) any person who has given notice of not less than sixty days, in the manner prescribed, of the`
  line `alleged offence and of his intention to make a complaint to the Board or officer authorised as`
  line aforesaid,
  line
  line `and no court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class shall`
  line `try any offence punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a complaint has been made under clause (b) of sub-section (1), the Board shall, on demand`
  line `by such person, make available the relevant reports in its possession to that person:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may refuse to make any such report available to such person if the same is, in`
  line `its opinion, against the public interest.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (28733)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 53
  title `Members, officers and employees of Board to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28733&sectionno=44&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `All the members and all`
  line `officers and other employees of a Board when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder shall be deemed to be public servants within the`
  line `meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (28734)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 54
  title `Reports and returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28734&sectionno=45&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The Central Board shall, in relation to its functions under this Act,`
  line `furnish to the Central Government, and a State Board shall, in relation to its functions under this Act,`
  line `furnish to the State Government and to the Central Board such reports, returns, statistics, accounts and`
  line `other information as that Government, or, as the case may be, the Central Board may, from time to time,`
  line require.
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (28735)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 55
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28735&sectionno=46&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or proceeding in`
  line `respect of any matter which an Appellate Authority constituted under this Act is empowered by or under`
  line `this Act to determine, and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect of any`
  line `action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (28736)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power of State Government to supersede State Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28736&sectionno=47&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time the State`
  line `Government is of opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) that a State Board constituted under this Act has persistently made default in the performance`
  line `of the functions imposed on it by or under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do,`
  line
  line `the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, supersede the State Board for such`
  line `period, not exceeding six months, as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing a notification under this sub-section for the reasons mentioned in`
  line `clause (a), the State Government shall give a reasonable opportunity to the State Board to show cause`
  line `why it should not be superseded and shall consider the explanations and objections, if any, of the`
  line `State Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the State Board,--`
  line
  line `(a) all the members shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under this Act, be exercised, performed`
  line `or discharged by the State Board shall, until the State Board is reconstituted under sub-section (3), be`
  line `exercised, performed or discharged by such person or persons as the State Government may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) all property owned or controlled by the State Board shall, until the Board is reconstituted`
  line `under sub-section (3), vest in the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the State Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) extend the period of supersession for such further term, not exceeding six months, as it may`
  line `consider necessary; or`
  line
  line `(b) reconstitute the State Board by a fresh nomination or appointment, as the case may be, and in`
  line `such case any person who vacated his office under clause (a) of sub-section (2) shall also be eligible`
  line `for nomination or appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may at any time before the expiration of the period of`
  line `supersession, whether originally specified under sub-section (1) or as extended under this sub-section,`
  line `take action under clause (b) of this sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (28737)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 57
  title `Special provision in the case of supersession of the Central Board or the State Boards constituted under the Water (Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1974.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28737&sectionno=48&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Where the Central`
  line `Board or any State Board constituted under the Water (Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1974`
  line `(Act 6 of 1974), is superseded by the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be,`
  line `under that Act, all the powers, functions and duties of the Central Board or such State Board under this`
  line `Act shall be exercised, performed or discharged during the period of such supersession by the person or`
  line `persons, exercising, preforming or discharging the powers, functions and duties of the Central Board or`
  line `such State Board under the Water (Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1974, during such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (28738)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 58
  title `Dissolution of State Boards constituted under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28738&sectionno=49&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) As and when the Water`
  line `(Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1974 (Act 6 of 1974), comes into force in any State and the`
  line `State Government constitutes ^1`
  line `[State Pollution Control Board] under that Act, the State Board constituted`
  line `by the State Government under this Act shall stand dissolved and the Board first-mentioned shall exercise`
  line `the powers and perform the functions of the Board second-mentioned in that State.`
  line
  line `(2) On the dissolution of the State Board constituted under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) all the members shall vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all moneys and other property of whatever kind (including the fund of the State Board) owned`
  line `by, or vested in, the State Board, immediately before such dissolution, shall stand transferred to and`
  line `vest in the^2`
  line `[State Pollution Control Board];`
  line
  line `(c) every officer and other employee serving under the State Board immediately before such`
  line `dissolution shall be transferred to and become an officer or other employee of the ^2`
  line `[State Pollution`
  line `Control Board] and hold office by the same tenure and at the same remuneration and on the same`
  line `terms and conditions of service as he would have held the same if the State Board constituted under`
  line `this Act had not been dissolved and shall continue to do so unless and until such tenure, remuneration`
  line `and terms and conditions of service are duly altered by the ^2`
  line `[State Pollution Control Board]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the tenure, remuneration and terms and conditions of service of any such officer or`
  line `other employee shall not be altered to his disadvantage without the previous sanction of the State`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(d) all liabilities and obligations of the State Board of whatever kind, immediately before such`
  line `dissolution, shall be deemed to be the liabilities or obligations, as the case may be, of the ^2`
  line [State
  line `Pollution Control Board] and any proceeding or cause of action, pending or existing immediately`
  line `before such dissolution by or against the State Board constituted under this Act in relation to such`
  line `liability or obligation may be continued and enforced by or against the ^2`
  line `[State Pollution Control`
  line Board.]
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 15, for "State Board for the Prevention and Control of Water Pollution" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 15 for "State Board for the Prevention and Control of Water Pollution" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (28739)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 59
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28739&sectionno=50&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `[Power to amend the Schedule.].--Omitted by the Air (Prevention and Control of`
  line `Pollution)Amendment Act, 1987 (47 of 1987), s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (28740)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 60
  title `Maintenance of register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28740&sectionno=51&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Board shall maintain a register containing particulars`
  line `of the persons to whom consent has been granted under section 21, the standards for emission laid down`
  line `by it in relation to each such consent and such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The register maintained under sub-section (1) shall be open to inspection at all reasonable hours`
  line `by any person interested in or affected by such standards for emission or by any other person authorised`
  line `by such person in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (28741)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 61
  title `Effect of other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28741&sectionno=52&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided by or under the Atomic Energy Act, 1962`
  line `(33 of 1962), in relation to radioactive air pollution the provisions of this Act shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (28742)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 62
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 23, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28742&sectionno=53&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, in`
  line `consultation with the Central Board, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules in respect of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the intervals and the time and place at which meetings of the Central Board or any committee`
  line `thereof shall be held and the procedure to be followed at such meetings, including the quorum`
  line `necessary for the transaction of business thereat, under sub-section (1) of section 10 and under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(b) the fees and allowances to be paid to the members of a committee of the Central Board, not`
  line `being members of the Board, under sub-section (3) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which and the purposes for which persons may be associated with the Central`
  line `Board under sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(d) the fees and allowance to be paid under sub-section (3) of section 12 to persons associated`
  line `with the Central Board under sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(e) the functions to be performed by the Central Board under clause (j) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(f) the form in which and the time within which the budget of the Central Board may be`
  line `prepared and forwarded to the Central Government under section 34;`
  line
  line `(ff) the form in which the annual report of die Central Board may be prepared under section 35;]`
  line
  line `(g) the form in which the accounts of the Central Board may be maintained under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 36.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (28743)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 63
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114&sectionId=28743&sectionno=54&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00004_198114_1517807322114
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3),`
  line `the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of`
  line `this Act in respect of matter not falling within the purview of section 53.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(a) the qualifications, knowledge and experience of scientific, engineering or management`
  line `aspects of pollution control required for appointment as member-secretary of a State Board`
  line `constituted under the Act;]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(aa)] the terms and conditions of service of the Chairman and other members (other than the`
  line `member-secretary) of the State Board constituted under this Act under sub-section (7) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) the intervals and the time and place at which meetings of the State Board or any committee`
  line `thereof shall be held and the procedure to be followed at such meetings, including the quorum`
  line `necessary for the transaction of business thereat, under sub-section (1) of section 10 and under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) the fees and allowances to be paid to the members of a committee of the State Board, not`
  line `being members of the Board under sub-section (3) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which and the purpose for which persons may be associated with the State`
  line `Board under sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(e) the fees and allowances to be paid under sub-section (3) of section 12 to persons associated`
  line `with the State Board under sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(f) the terms and conditions of service of the member-secretary of a State Board constituted under`
  line `this Act under sub-section (1) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(g) the powers and duties to be exercised and discharged by the member-secretary of a State`
  line `Board under sub-section (2) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(h) the conditions subject to which a State Board may appoint such officers and other employees`
  line `as it considers necessary for the efficient performance of its functions under sub-section (3) of section`
  line 14;
  line
  line `(i) the conditions subject to which a State Board may appoint a consultant under sub-section (5)`
  line `of section 14;`
  line
  line `(j) the functions to be performed by the State Board under clause (i) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner in which any area or areas may be declared as air pollution control area or areas`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(l) the form of application for the consent of the State Board, the fees payable therefore the period`
  line `within which such application shall be made and the particulars it may contain, under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(m) the procedure to be followed in respect of an inquiry under sub-section (3) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(n) the authorities or agencies to whom information under sub-section (1) of section 23 shall be`
  line furnished;
  line
  line `(o) the manner in which samples of air or emission may be taken under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line
  line `(p) the form of the notice referred to in sub-section (3) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(q) the form of the report of the State Board analyst under sub-section (1) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(r) the form of the report of the Government analyst under sub-section (3) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(s) the functions of the State Air Laboratory, the procedure for the submission to the said`
  line `Laboratory of samples of air or emission for analysis or tests, the form of Laboratory’s report thereon,`
  line `the fees payable in respect of such report and other matters as may be necessary or expedient to`
  line `enable that Laboratory to carry out its functions, under sub-section (2) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(t) the qualifications required for Government analysts under sub-section (1) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(u) the qualification required for State Board analysts under sub-section (2) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(v) the form and the manner in which appeals may be preferred, the fees payable in respect of`
  line `such appeals and the procedure to be followed by the Appellate Authority in disposing of the appeals`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 31;`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(w) the form in which and the time within which the budget of the State Board may be prepared`
  line `and forwarded to the State Government under section 34;`
  line
  line `(ww) the form in which the annual report of the State Board may be prepared under section 35;]`
  line
  line `(x) the form in which the accounts of the State Board may be maintained under the`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 36;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(xx) the manner in which notice of intention to make a complaint shall be given under`
  line `section 43;]`
  line
  line `(y) the particulars which the register maintained under section 51 may contain;`
  line
  line `(z) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) After the first constitution of the State Board, no rule with respect to any of the matters referred to`
  line `in sub-section (2) [other than those referred to ^5`
  line `[[in clause (aa)]] thereof], shall be made, varied, amended`
  line `or repealed without consulting that Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2 Clause (a) renumbered as clause (aa) thereof by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 47 of 1987, s. 24, for clause (w) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `4 Ins. by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `5 Subs. by s. 24,ibid.,for "in clause (a)" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
